  • These are results that I presented during our last meeting, but organized by AET and deficit values.

  • Is there a consistent effect of Deficit or AET bin size?

Summary:

  • Using square-root transformed data results in higher overall classification accuracy compared to raw data.

  • Perhaps the result of the “dynamic” climate bin size: smaller bins for lower values of AET and Deficit, larger bins for high values of AET and Deficit.
